text: Nectandra warmingii is a species of plant in the family Lauraceae. It is endemic to savanna regions of Bahia and Minas Gerais states in Brazil. ==References== warmingii Category:Endemic flora of Brazil Category:Flora of Bahia Category:Flora of Minas Gerais Category:Near threatened flora of South America Category:Taxa named by Carl Meissner Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
